<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="39" start="start">Diagnosis</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hook fil" authorityYear="1890" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Machilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Machilus kingii" order="Laurales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kingii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Machilus kingii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hook.f. in leaf shape and size, and short panicles less than 5.5 cm long, but distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hook fil" authorityYear="1890" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Machilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Machilus kingii" order="Laurales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kingii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Machilus kingii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its naked bud (vs. bud covered with scales in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hook fil" authorityYear="1890" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Machilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Machilus kingii" order="Laurales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kingii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Machilus kingii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), lamina foveolate on both surfaces (vs. obscure on lower surface), fewer flowers per panicle (3-5 vs. 4-9), and smaller perianth lobes (2 mm vs. 3-3.5 mm long).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
